2.10	1951_Pan_American_Games	1951 Pan American Games	The 1951 Pan American Games (the I Pan American Games) were held in Buenos Aires, Argentina between 25 February-9 March 1951. The Pan American Games' origins were at the Games of the X Olympiad in Los Angeles, United States, where officials representing the National Olympic Committees of the Americas discussed the staging of an Olympic-style regional athletic competition for the athletes of the Americas.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1c/Pan_am_1951.jpg/200px-Pan_am_1951.jpg
